	<section class="article-content clearfix" itemprop="articleBody">
		<p>Persivia provides evidence-based clinical decision support and actionable analytics to provide real-time clinical data to improve outcomes and ensure compliance for Meaningful Use Reporting.</p>
<h4>Establishing The Proper Technology Framework</h4>
<p>In addition to meeting clinical requirements, the underlying CDS technology framework must be easy to deploy, easy to maintain, flexible, and extensible.<br />Persiviaâ€™s physicians rigorously review hundreds of medical journals, texts, and physician associations, to develop clinical summaries and distill evidence-based guidelines. All guidelines are scored and prioritized to ensure relevancy. At the same time, clinician-friendly content authoring tools in the platform allow for self-customization; there is no need for programmer involvement.</p>
<p>The underlying technology is Web-service-oriented from the ground up, and designed to exchange data with existing systems employing all commonly used standards, vocabularies, and messaging modalities. The system combines all available patient data with the embedded guidelines to create order sets, alerts and multi-level reports to identify and report on problem areas and gaps in care.</p>
<h4><strong>Partner with Persivia to:</strong></h4>
<h6>Meet Requirements</h6>
<ul>
<li>Satisfy all Meaningful Use requirements, including reporting on all CQMs (Clinical Quality Measures)</li>
<li>Deliver real-time clinical decision support</li>
<li>Offer in-patient and ambulatory, patient-specific order sets</li>
<li>Deliver patient education materials at the point-of-care</li>
</ul>
<h6>Satisfy Clients</h6>
<ul>
<li>Meet CDS, order sets, and clinical analytics demands</li>
<li>Address growing reporting and quality measurement needs</li>
<li>Enable clients to achieve full compliance with Meaningful Use with one integration</li>
</ul>
<h6>Achieve Easy Integration</h6>
<ul>
<li>Collect all clinical content into one IT domain</li>
<li>Leverage templated yet customizable content libraries</li>
<li>Implement quickly with an HL7v3.0/2.X SOA architecture</li>
</ul>	</section>
	
